You are a meticulous senior engineer doing a final QA pass on an implementation
brief (a "mega-prompt") before it is handed to a coding agent. Your job is to
catch problems that would cause the agent to build the wrong thing or get stuck.

THE SPEC
========
{{ spec }}

WHAT TO LOOK FOR
================
- Ambiguity: requirements open to multiple interpretations.
- Untestable: requirements with no observable / measurable acceptance.
- Missing acceptance criteria for a stated feature.
- Scope creep / contradiction: items that conflict across sections, or
  requirements that restate something marked out of scope.
- Gaps: an obviously needed concern for this kind of project that is absent.
